Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.58,0:41:45.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离地约600英里的高度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}approximately 600 miles above our planet's surface. 
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.25,0:41:53.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在太空中 物体可以滞留数千年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In space, objects can stay for tens to hundreds of years 
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.21,0:41:55.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为那里没有空气阻力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because there's no air resistance. 
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.97,0:42:00.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是它们最终会经历轨道衰减\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But they will eventually undergo orbital decay. 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.72,0:42:01.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们会失去能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They will lose energy 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.01,0:42:04.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为有很小的大气阻力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because there's very little atmospheric drag, 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.73,0:42:08.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球重力会把它们拽回大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the Earth's gravity will tug them back down into its atmosphere. 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.77,0:42:13.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卫星回落 有时很快 有时则要经过很长时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Satellites fall back, sometimes quickly and sometimes over a long period, 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.32,0:42:16.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只是因为它们开始接触到一点大气层时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}simply because they begin to touch a little bit 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.40,0:42:18.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大气层足以有一个增强的力道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the atmosphere, enough of the atmosphere 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.53,0:42:21.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,加持较长的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that there's an increasing force over a long period of time. 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.95,0:42:24.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,较小的力道 坚持较长的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that small force, acting over a long time, 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.29,0:42:26.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,基本上会将它们拉出轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will basically drag them out of orbit, 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.21,0:42:27.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终重新返回\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they will eventually re-enter. 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.88,0:42:34.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大部分碎片在重返大气层时会燃烧和蒸发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most debris burns up during atmospheric re-entry and vaporizes. 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.84,0:42:38.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而有些碎片出自较坚固的部件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, some pieces are made of stronger components, 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.97,0:42:43.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,诸如不锈钢 钛 能够耐住高温\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}such as stainless steel and titanium, which can survive tremendous heat. 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.35,0:42:49.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦越过了大气层的稠密区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once below the dense regions of the atmosphere, 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.52,0:42:51.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们就落到地面上了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they literally free-fall to the ground. 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.86,0:42:55.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会以很低的速度落下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It'll hit at a very low velocity, 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.48,0:42:59.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是每秒150英尺或时速150英里 那个样子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}say 150 feet per second or 150 miles an hour, something like that. 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.20,0:43:01.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以那就是问题所在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so that's the problem. 
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.16,0:43:02.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以你基本上是在把物体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So you're basically slowing something 
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.58,0:43:06.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在较短的时间里 从轨道速度减慢到静止\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from an orbital speed down to essentially nothing in a relatively short time. 
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.00,0:43:08.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,主发动机点火\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Main engine start. 
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.79,0:43:11.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,国际航天界现在对大多数物体规定了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The international space community now imposes 
